Uses [Cheerio](https://cheerio.js.org/index.html)
Please refer to the [documentation](https://cheerio.js.org/classes/Cheerio.html) for available functions.
## Input
```js
<any>
```

## Output
```js
{
	result: <the data returned from the code>,
	input: <incomming data>
}
```

## Example code
```js
// instance : component instance
// $: cheerio instance
// html: html string

var txt = [];
$('ul > li').each(function (i, elem) {
	txt.push($(this).text());
});
return txt;
```

The component is extraordinary because it must be executed directly from the source code via the `flowstream.exec()` method. The component triggers received data into the Flow.

```js
var opt = {};
opt.id = 'ID_OF_EXEC_INSTANCE';
opt.data = { custom: 'data' };
opt.callback = function(err, msg) {
	// msg.uid;
	// msg.ref;
	// msg.repo {Object}
	// msg.data {Object}
	// msg.cloned {Number} how many times was the message cloned?
	// msg.duration {Number} in milliseconds
};

// optional:
// opt.vars = {};    --> custom variables
// opt.repo = {};    --> custom repository data and this data will be returned in the callback
// opt.uid;          --> for storing some unique ID
// opt.ref;          --> for storing some reference ID
flowinstance.exec(opt);
```

InfluxDB

## Input
Expected data for "Write data":
```javascript
{
    measurement: '<measurement-name>',
	fields: {
        fieldname: <fieldvalue>,
    },
    tags: {
        tagname: '<tagvalue>'
    }
}
```

Expected data for "Execute a Flux query":
```javascript
{
    query: 'from(bucket: "Some Bucket") |> range(start: -1h)'
}
```

The code defined in this component can be executed by multiple `Middleware Exec`.
**Example:**
```js
// available arguments
// instance {FlowStreamComponent}
// $        {FlowStreamMessage}
// data     reference to $.data
// repo     reference to $.repo
// vars     reference to instance.main.variables

if (data.headers['x-token'] === instance.main.variables.token)
	// data will be send to `Output` output of `Middleware Exec` component
	callback(null, data);
else
	// data will be send to `Error` output of `Middleware Exec` component
	callback('an error occured');
```

MQTT Publish

Input:
```javascript
{
	topic: 'some/topic',
	message: { some: 'data' },
	// optional
	options: {
		qos: 0|1|2,
		retain: true|false
	}
}
```

## Output
```js
{
	"ts": 1646643556666,      // timestamp
	"ignorelist": []          // list of ignored devices, the devices not in the "Name/ID map" in config form
	"sensors": [
		{
			"id": "28-3c01e076b84d", // onewire sensor id
			"name": "livingroom",    // friedly name assigned in the config form
			"value": 21.06,          // current value
			// optionaly, if enabled, the last 10 values, 1st(21.06) is most recent
			"history": [ 21.06, 21.13, 21.06, 21.06, 21.13, 21.13, 21.06, 21.06, 21.08, 21.09 ],
		},
		...
]
```

The component splits a message with an array of objects on the input into separate messages with individual objects on the output.

__Input example__:

```js
[
	{
		"email": "michal@totaljs.com",
		"date": 20220202,
		"meno": "Michal Klacan"
	},
	{
		"email": "martin@totaljs.com",
		"date": 20220204,
		"meno": "Martin Smola"
	},
	{
		"email": "peter@totaljs.com",
		"datum": 20220210,
		"meno": "Peter Sirka"
	}
]
```

__Output example__:

```js
